# Cochinita Pibil

Based on [https://www.cilantroparsley.com/cochinita-pibil-instant-pot/](https://www.cilantroparsley.com/cochinita-pibil-instant-pot/)

{ rating="0" image="None.jpeg" }
:::
:::

## Ingredients

### Pork

- [ ] 3-4 pounds pork shoulder
- [ ] 4 oz achiote paste
- [ ] 6 oranges, freshly squeezed (or 1 cup orange juice)
- [ ] 5 limes, squeezed

### Optional Pickled Onion

- [ ] 1/2 red onion, sliced
- [ ] 1/2 cup water
- [ ] 1/2 cup white vinegar
- [ ] 1 tsp coriander or cumin
- [ ] 2 bay leaves

### Garnish

- [ ] Chopped cilantro
- [ ] Lime wedges
- [ ] Pickled onion

## Recipe

1. Make the sauce: Blend achiote paste, orange juice, and lime juice until smooth. Add to pork and marinate overnight (minimum one hour if time-limited).
1. Instant Pot method: Place all ingredients in Instant Pot and pressure cook on high for 1 hour.
1. Oven method: Preheat to 325°F. Line baking dish with three sheets aluminum foil. Add pork with marinade. Cover with three more foil sheets, seal well. Bake 3-4 hours.
1. Slow cooker method: Add all ingredients. Cook on high 3-4 hours or low 6-7 hours.
1. Shred the pork: Using a slotted spoon, transfer pork to bowl. Shred with two forks. Pour sauce back over meat.
1. Optional pickled onions: Simmer onion, water, vinegar, coriander, and bay leaves 2-3 minutes. Cool, refrigerate 1 hour.
1. Garnish: Top with cilantro, lime wedges, and/or pickled onions.
1. Serve on rice, tortillas, or gorditas.

## Notes

- Don’t trim fat—it provides essential flavor
- Seal foil tightly when baking
- Tastes better the next day as flavors develop
